sql:
SELECT SUM(duration) AS total_duration
FROM extension_usage
WHERE extension_id = 0 AND user_id = 0;

SELECT MAX(duration) AS max_usage_duration
FROM extension_usage
WHERE extension_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
Frequently used extensions are those that have been used more than 10 times; 
User ratings refer to the average feedback provided by users, which is a score between 0 and 1; 
Usage time refers to the average duration of usage; 
Average content quality refers to the average content quality rating of the publisher, which is a score between 0 and 1.

sql:
SELECT update_description
FROM extension_updates
WHERE INSTR(update_description, 'Added new feature') > 0;

SELECT publisher_id
FROM reputations
WHERE trustworthiness = (
  SELECT MAX(trustworthiness)
  FROM reputations
);

SELECT extension_id
FROM extension_permissions
WHERE permission_type IN ('block', 'lock', 'restrict');
